      "safety": "/ Technique Tips\n* Keep spine neutral and core braced — avoid excessive lower-back arching; control your lumbar/hip posture throughout.\n* Use a vertical bar path — press straight up; avoid pushing the bar far forward, which causes leverage and back stress.\n* Start with light or no weight if you’re new — master shoulder mobility, stability, control before loading heavy.\n* Ensure feet shoulder-width, stable base, slight knee bend — this aids balance and prevents lower-body involvement turning the lift into a “push press.”\n* Avoid using leg or hip drive — if knees or hips move significantly, you might be doing a push press rather than strict overhead press. For strict press, keep lower body stable."
