      "benefits": "& Why Use Bench Press\n* Effective upper-body strength and mass builder — because it engages multiple major muscle groups (chest, shoulders, triceps) and stabilizers, bench press is among the most efficient exercises for chest and upper-body development.\n* Helps improve functional pushing strength — translates to real-life tasks (pushing, lifting) and improves performance in sports or everyday movement.\n* Allows progressive overload & strength scaling — you can gradually increase weight (plates) to drive strength/hypertrophy gains, while ensuring stabilization and form remain stable.\n* Contributes to balanced upper-body development when combined with pulling/back exercises — good for aesthetic symmetry and posture if paired with back-work.",
