      "benefits": "& Why Use Plank\n* Core strength and spinal support: Planks are among the most effective isometric exercises for building core stability, supporting spine health, and improving functional strength for daily activities.\n* Posture improvement: Regular planking helps reinforce proper spinal alignment, improving posture and countering issues from prolonged sitting or poor posture.\n* Full-body stability and balance: Because multiple muscle groups are engaged simultaneously, planks help develop overall body stability, balance, and muscular endurance.\n* Convenience & accessibility: No equipment needed, minimal space required — planks can be done almost anywhere, making them ideal for home workouts or warm-ups.\n* Injury prevention and spine health: A strong, stable core helps support joints and spine during heavier lifts or daily movements, reducing risk of back pain or injury.",
